This paper deals with automated parsing of mathematical expressions, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of statistical learning and automated theorem proving, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of alignment techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with large-theory automated theorem proving, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
